<subSubSection id="C320D0AAFFEC983F039EFC2456C1FB3E" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B858321FFEC983F039EFC2456C1FB3E" blockId="34.[151,1437,1000,1453]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="B94E5F33FFEC983F039EFC245764FBA3" box="[151,371,1000,1025]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis of male.</emphasis>
This species can be recognized by its small size, the moderately emarginate mandibles, the small marginal cell that is shorter than the stigma measured along the costal margin, the lack of mesosternal processes, and the lack of plumose setae even along the margins of the metasomal tergites. The genitalia are similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3AF8A2FFEC983F0206FB90577CFBD7" box="[271,363,1116,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="becki">
<emphasis id="B94E5F33FFEC983F0206FB90577CFBD7" box="[271,363,1116,1141]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. becki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13019FA4FFEC983F0275FB9057D2FBD4" box="[380,453,1116,1142]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[186,1429,263,1694]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,224,1790]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Lateral view of genitalia. 1. Acanthophotopsis falciformis; 2. Sphaeropthalma becki; 3. S. difficilis; 4. S." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188393/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF29106FFEC983F02BDFB9057D2FBD4" box="[436,453,1116,1142]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
), but have an extremely short cuspis that barely surpasses the penis valve in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
